race.comment: VIM VITAE (10) will show more third-up and finally draws an inside barrier. Covered ground after a slow start at Bendigo this trip and has the blinkers applied for the first time. TOP REWARD (9) debuts for the local Clayton Douglas yard and owns a string of placings at the jumpouts. The colt looks talented and ready to go. Dee is a positive jockey booking. WAILEA (12) has her third race start and is showing enough to suggest she's a chance. Maps well and the step up in trip will suit. SQUARE DEAL (2) wasn't beaten far at Sale over 1425m first up and is sure to build on that. Include on an each-way basis.
